==English==
===Etymology===
Latin [[conferre]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/kən'fɜ:/}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|confer|confers|conferred|conferring}}
# ''(obsolete, transitive)'' To bring together, [[collect]]
# ''(intransitive)'' To have [[discourse]]; to consult, [[discuss]]; to compare views; to deliberate.
# ''(obsolete, intransitive)'' To contribute (to); to [[conduce]].
# ''(transitive)'' To [[grant]] as a possession; to [[bestow]].

<!---- Specifically, ''to compare'', as a translation of the [[abbreviation]] ''[[cf.]]''. — This is wrong! cf. is an abbreviation of LATIN 'confer', which means 'compare' ------>

